    <title><literal>SetAMAFlags()</literal></title>

    <indexterm significance="preferred">
      <primary>Dialplan Applications</primary>

      <secondary><code>SetAMAFlags()</code></secondary>
    </indexterm>

    <simpara>Sets AMA-Flags in the Call Detail Record (CDR).</simpara>

    <synopsis><command>SetAMAFlags(<replaceable>flags</replaceable>)</command></synopsis>

    <simpara>Sets AMA (Automatic Message Accounting)<footnote>
        <para>In North America, Automatic Message Accounting has been used for
        billing in Direct Distance Dialing since it was introduced in the
        mid-20th century. The system was originally used to provide the toll
        system with information about the originating circuit so that the
        subscriber could be billed for a long distance call.</para>
      </footnote> flags in the CDR. Overrides any settings found in channel
    configuration files. Valid settings are <code>default</code>,
    <code>omit</code>, <code>billing</code> and
    <code>documentation</code>.</simpara>

    <simpara>Returns 0.</simpara>

    <programlisting>exten =&gt; 123,1,SetAMAFlags(billing)</programlisting>

